MESSAGE.value: Wrote Data class to express fetched DependentData and stored in a MongoDB. Wrote fetchPersons() that creates a Person from each UNI. Writing fetchUnis(), but need two pass 2-factor auth to access the pages, so I'm going to use Selenium, authenticate myself, and then let the WebDriver do the rest.

Got fetchUnis() to work!
A request to a certain page sometimes partially fails, in that it returns the wrong page or unis on other pages, meaning I'm not certain that I have all the unis. (There are overlaps between students and faculty/staff, but these are real overlaps, and should be kept).
To solve this, I wrote OkHttpClient.readPaginatedRetrying(), which, given a find num pages and num items function, keeps sequentially requesting all the pages until all of the items are found.
I have a bunch of debug code lying around. I wanted to commit them and then clean them up in case I need them again.
